Installing and Configuring Alembic:\
1. Install Alembic ("pip install alembic")\
2. Create migration environment ("alembic init alembic")\
3. In alembic.ini, edit "sqlalchemy.url =" to match URI of database\
e.g. sqlalchemy.url = sqlite:////Users/cicero/hackerschool/project_muselon/test.db\
4. In env.py, replace "target_metadata = None" with\
import os, sys\
sys.path.append(os.getcwd())\
from muselon import models\
target_metadata = models.db.metadata\
5. Create new revision ("alembic revision -m "create first revision"")\
populate resulting script's upgrade() and downgrade() functions.\
6. Run first migration ("alembic upgrade head")\
(Optionally, in environment.py set compare_type=True)\
\
7. Autogenerate future revisions ("alembic revision --autogenerate -m "new revision"")\
8. Follow up with "alembic upgrade head", "python init_db.py"\
